.SH "NAME"
git-cai \- AI\-powered commit message generator
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
.nf
\f(CRgit cai\fP [\-A | \-\-amend] [\-a | \-\-all] [\-C | \-\-conventional]
        [\-b | \-\-branch] [\-c | \-\-crazy] [\-d | \-\-debug]
        [\-F | \-\-full\-files] [\-f PATH | \-\-files PATH]
        [\-g | \-\-generate\-config]
        [\-H KEY=VALUE | \-\-set\-home KEY=VALUE] [\-h | \-\-help]
        [\-i | \-\-install\-completion]
        [\-l [config|editor|language|model|path|provider|style] |
         \-\-list [config|editor|language|model|path|provider|style]]
        [\-m MODEL | \-\-model MODEL]
        [\-P PROVIDER | \-\-provider PROVIDER] [\-p | \-\-generate\-prompts]
        [\-S KEY=VALUE | \-\-set KEY=VALUE]
        [\-s [N|HASH] | \-\-squash [N|HASH]]
        [\-T SECONDS | \-\-timeout SECONDS]
        [\-t | \-\-time] [\-u | \-\-update] [\-v | \-\-version]
        [\-x CONTEXT | \-\-context CONTEXT]
.fi
.br
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
git\-cai is a Git extension that generates commit
messages from staged changes using AI.
.sp
The command is invoked as \f(CRgit cai\fP and integrates into Git using the
standard Git extension mechanism.
.sp
git\-cai behaves like \f(CRgit commit\fP, but with the commit message pre\-filled:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
It reads the staged diff (\f(CRgit diff \-\-cached\fP).
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
It sends the diff to the configured LLM provider/model.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
It opens your configured Git editor so you can review/edit before committing.
.RE
.SH "SETUP"
.sp
First run / configuration:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Run \f(CRgit cai\fP once. If no config exists yet, git\-cai creates:
\f(CR~/.config/cai/cai_config.yml\fP (global config) and ensures default prompt files exist:
\f(CR~/.config/cai/commit_prompt.md\fP and \f(CR~/.config/cai/squash_prompt.md\fP.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Add at least one API key to \f(CR~/.config/cai/tokens.yml\fP (created as a template if missing).
The YAML keys are provider names (for example: \f(CRopenai\fP, \f(CRanthropic\fP, \f(CRgemini\fP,
\f(CRgroq\fP, \f(CRxai\fP, \f(CRmistral\fP, \f(CRdeepseek\fP).
If you use \f(CRollama\fP as provider, no token is required.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
In \f(CR~/.config/cai/cai_config.yml\fP, set \f(CRdefault:\fP to the provider you want and
adjust the provider block (model/temperature) as needed.
.RE
.sp
Repository\-specific setup (optional):
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Put a \f(CRcai_config.yml\fP (or \f(CRcai_config.yaml\fP) into the repository root.
This repository config is authoritative and is not merged with the home config.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Generate a starting point with \f(CRgit cai \-g\fP (creates \f(CRcai_config.yml\fP in the
current directory).
.RE
.sp
Custom prompts (optional):
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Generate prompt files in the current directory with \f(CRgit cai \-p\fP.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Point \f(CRprompt_file\fP / \f(CRsquash_prompt_file\fP in \f(CRcai_config.yml\fP to your custom files.
.RE
.SH "OPTIONS"
.sp
\-A, \-\-amend
.RS 4
Regenerate and amend the last commit message. git\-cai reads the diff from
the most recent commit, sends it to the configured LLM, and opens the editor
so you can review or adjust the message before amending. This is useful when
the original commit message was poorly worded or when you want the LLM to
produce a better summary.
.sp
Combine with \f(CR\-c\fP to skip the editor and amend immediately.
.sp
Cannot be combined with \f(CR\-\-squash\fP or \f(CR\-\-list\fP.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-A
git cai \-A \-c
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-a, \-\-all
.RS 4
Stage all modified and deleted files that are already tracked by Git before
generating the commit message. This mirrors the behaviour of \f(CRgit commit \-a\fP.
Untracked (new) files are not staged; add them manually with \f(CRgit add\fP first.
.sp
Cannot be combined with \f(CR\-\-list\fP, \f(CR\-\-update\fP, or \f(CR\-\-squash\fP.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-a
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-b, \-\-branch
.RS 4
Include the current Git branch name as context when generating the commit
message. The LLM uses the branch name to better understand the intent and
scope of the changes (e.g., a branch named \f(CRfix/login\-timeout\fP hints at a
bug fix related to login timeouts).
.sp
This flag applies for the current invocation only. To enable it permanently,
set \f(CRbranch_context: true\fP in \f(CRcai_config.yml\fP or run:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-S branch_context=true
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-b
git cai \-b \-c
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-C, \-\-conventional
.RS 4
Generate the commit message in Conventional Commits format
(\f(CRtype(scope): description\fP). The LLM is instructed to use one of the
following types: \f(CRfeat\fP, \f(CRfix\fP, \f(CRdocs\fP, \f(CRstyle\fP, \f(CRrefactor\fP, \f(CRperf\fP, \f(CRtest\fP,
\f(CRbuild\fP, \f(CRci\fP, \f(CRchore\fP, \f(CRrevert\fP. Append \f(CR!\fP after the type or scope to
signal a breaking change.
.sp
This flag applies for the current invocation only. To enable it permanently,
set \f(CRconventional: true\fP in \f(CRcai_config.yml\fP or run:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-S conventional=true
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-C
git cai \-C \-c
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-c, \-\-crazy
.RS 4
Trust the LLM output and commit immediately without opening an editor.
The generated message is used as\-is. Useful in scripts or when you are
confident in the LLM output.
.sp
Can be combined with \f(CR\-A\fP to amend without review, or with \f(CR\-C\fP to commit
a Conventional Commits message directly.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-c
git cai \-A \-c
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-d, \-\-debug
.RS 4
Enable debug logging. Produces verbose output to stderr, including
configuration loading, provider selection, prompt assembly, and the raw
LLM request/response. Helpful for troubleshooting configuration or
provider issues.
.sp
Cannot be combined with \f(CR\-\-help\fP or \f(CR\-\-version\fP.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-d
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-F, \-\-full\-files
.RS 4
Send the full working\-tree contents of every staged file alongside the diff.
By default, git\-cai sends only the staged diff to the LLM. With \f(CR\-F\fP, the
diff is followed by a block of the form:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
\-\-\- File: path/to/file.py \-\-\-
<full contents>
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
for each staged text file. This produces higher\-quality commit messages for
large or context\-dependent changes, at the cost of more input tokens. Binary
files and files matching \f(CR.caiignore\fP are skipped.
.sp
The flag applies for the current invocation only. To enable it permanently,
set \f(CRfull_files: true\fP in \f(CRcai_config.yml\fP or run:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-S full_files=true
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
Can be combined with \f(CR\-f\fP to scope the content dump to specific files.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-F
git cai \-F \-f src/foo.py
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-f, \-\-files PATH
.RS 4
Restrict the diff (and full\-file content, if \f(CR\-F\fP is on) to the given path.
Repeat the flag to pass multiple paths. \f(CR.caiignore\fP patterns still apply on
top of the whitelist.
.sp
Useful when a working tree contains unrelated staged changes and the commit
should focus on a subset of them, or when you want the LLM to concentrate
on a specific file.
.sp
Cannot be used with \f(CR\-\-list\fP, \f(CR\-\-update\fP, or \f(CR\-\-squash\fP.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-f src/foo.py
git cai \-f src/foo.py \-f tests/test_foo.py
git cai \-F \-f src/foo.py
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-g, \-\-generate\-config
.RS 4
Write the default \f(CRcai_config.yml\fP into the current directory. This is a
convenient way to create a repository\-specific configuration that overrides
the home config. Edit the generated file to customise provider, model,
language, style, or other settings for this repository.
.sp
If a \f(CRcai_config.yml\fP already exists in the current directory, an error is
shown to prevent accidental overwrites.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
cd /path/to/repo
git cai \-g
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-H, \-\-set\-home KEY=VALUE
.RS 4
Set a configuration value in the home (default) config file at
\f(CR~/.config/cai/cai_config.yml\fP. Always targets the home config, even when a
repository\-level config exists. Use this to change your personal defaults
that apply to all repositories without a repo\-specific config.
.sp
Supports the same key formats as \f(CR\-\-set\fP, including dot notation for nested
provider keys.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-H language=de
git cai \-H default=anthropic
git cai \-H emoji=false
git cai \-H groq.model=llama\-3.3\-70b
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-h, \-\-help
.RS 4
Show a summary of available flags and usage information. When a manual page
is installed, the full manual is opened instead.
.RE
.sp
\-i, \-\-install\-completion
.RS 4
Install shell completion for \f(CRgit cai\fP. Supports bash, zsh, and fish.
Completions cover all flags and provider names for \f(CR\-\-provider\fP.
.sp
After installation, restart your terminal or source your shell configuration
file for the completions to take effect.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-i
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-l, \-\-list [config|editor|language|model|path|provider|style]
.RS 4
List information about a specific category. Provide one of the supported
list types as the next argument. Without an argument, a help text is shown
listing all valid choices.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-l config
git cai \-l editor
git cai \-l language
git cai \-l model
git cai \-l path
git cai \-l provider
git cai \-l style
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-m, \-\-model MODEL
.RS 4
Override the model for this invocation. Must be used together with
\f(CR\-\-provider\fP (\f(CR\-P\fP); specifying \f(CR\-\-model\fP alone is an error. The model name
is passed directly to the provider\(cqs API, so it must be a valid model
identifier for that provider.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-P openai \-m gpt\-4o
git cai \-P anthropic \-m claude\-haiku\-4\-5
git cai \-P ollama \-m mistral
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-P, \-\-provider PROVIDER
.RS 4
Override the LLM provider for this invocation. The model and temperature
from the configuration for that provider are used unless \f(CR\-\-model\fP is also
specified. Available providers: \f(CRanthropic\fP, \f(CRdeepseek\fP, \f(CRgemini\fP, \f(CRgroq\fP,
\f(CRmistral\fP, \f(CRollama\fP, \f(CRopenai\fP, \f(CRxai\fP.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-P anthropic
git cai \-P groq \-m llama\-3.3\-70b
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-p, \-\-generate\-prompts
.RS 4
Generate default \f(CRcommit_prompt.md\fP and \f(CRsquash_prompt.md\fP in the current
directory. These files serve as starting points for custom prompts. After
generating them, point \f(CRprompt_file\fP and/or \f(CRsquash_prompt_file\fP in your
\f(CRcai_config.yml\fP to the generated files.
.sp
If the files already exist, an error is shown to prevent accidental
overwrites.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-p
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-S, \-\-set KEY=VALUE
.RS 4
Set a configuration value in the repository config (\f(CRcai_config.yml\fP in the
repository root). Requires an existing repo config; if none is found, an
error is shown with a hint to use \f(CR\-\-set\-home\fP (\f(CR\-H\fP) to change the default
config or \f(CRgit cai \-g\fP to create a repo config first.
.sp
Supports dot notation for nested provider keys (e.g., \f(CRgroq.model\fP).
Values are auto\-parsed: \f(CRtrue\fP/\f(CRfalse\fP become booleans, numeric strings
become integers or floats, everything else stays a string.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-S default=anthropic
git cai \-S emoji=false
git cai \-S groq.model=llama\-3.3\-70b
git cai \-S openai.temperature=0.7
git cai \-S conventional=true
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-s, \-\-squash [N|HASH]
.RS 4
Squash commits on the current branch into a single commit with an
LLM\-generated summary message. git\-cai collects the individual commit
messages, sends them to the LLM, and opens the editor for review. After
confirmation, a soft reset is performed and the squashed commit is created.
.sp
Without an argument, all commits since the branch diverged from the base
branch are squashed (default behaviour).
.sp
With a number \f(CRN\fP, the last N commits are squashed. If N exceeds the number
of commits on this branch (since it diverged), a warning is shown and
confirmation is required. If N exceeds the total number of commits in the
repository, an error is shown and the operation is aborted.
.sp
With a commit hash, all commits from HEAD down to and including the given
commit are squashed. The commit must exist in the current branch history.
.sp
This rewrites history. A force push is required to update a remote branch.
git\-cai will prompt before executing the force push.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-s
git cai \-s 3
git cai \-s a1b2c3d
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-T, \-\-timeout SECONDS
.RS 4
Override the HTTP timeout for the LLM call in this invocation. The default
is 30 seconds for remote providers and 300 seconds for Ollama (since local
generation can be significantly slower). The override applies uniformly to
whichever provider is selected for this run.
.sp
To change the default permanently, set \f(CRtimeout: <seconds>\fP in
\f(CRcai_config.yml\fP or the home config:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-H timeout=60
git cai \-S timeout=45
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
Ollama keeps its own timeout under \f(CRollama.timeout\fP (default 300). Override
it separately:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-H ollama.timeout=600
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-T 60
git cai \-T 120 \-P anthropic
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-t, \-\-time
.RS 4
Measure and log the wall\-clock time taken to generate the commit message.
The duration is printed to stderr after the LLM responds. Useful for
comparing provider/model performance.
.sp
Can also be enabled permanently via \f(CRmeasure_time: true\fP in
\f(CRcai_config.yml\fP.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-t
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-u, \-\-update
.RS 4
Check PyPI for a newer version of git\-cai\-cli. If an update is available,
the new version number and the install command are printed.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-u
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-v, \-\-version
.RS 4
Print the installed version of git\-cai\-cli and exit. The version is derived
from git tags via \f(CRsetuptools\-scm\fP.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-v
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\-x, \-\-context CONTEXT
.RS 4
Provide extra context for the LLM to consider when generating the commit
message. The context string is appended to the diff before sending it to
the provider. This is useful for including information that is not visible
in the diff itself, such as a ticket number, the reason for a change, or
a link to an issue.
.sp
Can be combined with any commit\-generating mode (\f(CRCOMMIT\fP or \f(CRAMEND\fP).
Cannot be used with \f(CR\-\-list\fP, \f(CR\-\-update\fP, or \f(CR\-\-squash\fP.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-x "Fixes JIRA\-1234"
git cai \-x "Performance optimisation for the search endpoint"
git cai \-A \-x "Reword after code review feedback"
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.SH "LIST TYPES"
.sp
The argument to \f(CR\-\-list\fP must be one of the following:
.sp
config
.RS 4
Show the active (effective) configuration. This displays the fully resolved
configuration that git\-cai is currently using, including all provider blocks,
global settings, and any overrides from repository\-level config files.
.sp
This is useful for verifying which settings are in effect, especially when a
repository config overrides the home config. Nested provider blocks (model,
temperature) are displayed indented under their provider name.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-l config
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
Example output:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
Active configuration:

  default: groq
  language: en
  style: professional
  emoji: true
  groq:
    model: moonshotai/kimi\-k2\-instruct
    temperature: 0
  ...
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
editor
.RS 4
List supported and tested editors as default git editor. Most likely more
editors will work. git\-cai uses the same editor resolution as Git itself
(\f(CRGIT_EDITOR\fP, \f(CRVISUAL\fP, \f(CREDITOR\fP environment variables).
.RE
.sp
language
.RS 4
List all 121 supported languages for commit message generation. Languages
are displayed sorted alphabetically by their human\-readable name, each
followed by their language code. The language code is what you set in
\f(CRcai_config.yml\fP under the \f(CRlanguage\fP key.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-l language
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
Example output (excerpt):
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
Available languages:
  \- English → en
  \- French → fr
  \- German → de
  \- Japanese → ja
  \- Klingon → tlh
  ...
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
model
.RS 4
Show the default model for each supported provider. This displays the model
name that git\-cai uses out of the box if no custom model is configured.
Models are listed alphabetically by provider name.
.sp
Note: these are the built\-in defaults. If you have overridden a model in
your \f(CRcai_config.yml\fP, the override is not shown here. Use \f(CR\-\-list config\fP
to see the effective configuration including overrides.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-l model
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
Example output:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
Default models:

  anthropic\&    → claude\-haiku\-4\-5
  deepseek\&     → deepseek\-chat
  gemini\&       → gemini\-2.5\-flash
  groq\&         → moonshotai/kimi\-k2\-instruct
  mistral\&      → codestral\-2508
  ollama\&       → llama3.1
  openai\&       → gpt\-5.2
  xai\&          → grok\-4\-1\-fast\-reasoning
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
path
.RS 4
Show all resolved configuration file paths. This displays the locations
of the config directory, home config file, tokens file, and whether a
repository\-specific config file is present. The active config source
(repository or home) is shown at the bottom.
.sp
This is particularly useful for debugging configuration issues or when
you are unsure which config file git\-cai is reading.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-l path
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
Example output (no repo config):
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
Configuration file paths:

  Config directory:\&      /home/user/.config/cai
  Home config:\&           /home/user/.config/cai/cai_config.yml
