.sp
style
.RS 4
Show available commit message styles with descriptions and examples. The
style controls the tone of the generated commit message. Set the style in
\f(CRcai_config.yml\fP or override it per invocation with \f(CR\-\-set style=<name>\fP.
.sp
Available styles: \f(CRacademic\fP, \f(CRapologetic\fP, \f(CRexcited\fP, \f(CRfriendly\fP, \f(CRfunny\fP,
\f(CRneutral\fP, \f(CRnone\fP, \f(CRprofessional\fP (default), \f(CRsarcastic\fP.
.sp
The special style \f(CRnone\fP omits the style instruction from the prompt
entirely, letting the model choose its own tone.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git cai \-l style
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
